Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Put some #baking trays{} in the oven.

> You may be able to fit two pizzas on one tray, depending on the size of your tray, or use more trays if necessary.

Cut the @Premium Tomato Mix{1}(in half through the equator). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Tear each @serrano ham{1} slice into roughly four or five bite-sized pieces. Cut the @black olives{30} in half. Cut each @mozzarella{1} ball into eight slices, then tear each slice into about four or five small-ish pieces (it doesn't have to be exact). Remove the @basil{1} leaves from their stalks, roughly chop the stalks and half the leaves (leave the rest of the leaves whole for garnish later).

Put a #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} and add your garlic and basil stalks. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @tomato passata{1} and add your chopped basil leaves. Sprinkle in a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind} and stir everything together. Simmer gently for ~{5-6%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat.

While your sauce cooks, roll out your @Northern Dough Co. Pizza Dough{2}! Dust your work surface with some flour, if you have some. If not, place your dough between two large sheets of #clingfilm{} (so it doesn't stick to your work surface!). Roll out into rounds roughly 25cm across.

> If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle wrapped in clingfilm.

Carefully take the baking trays out of your oven and place your pizza bases on them. Divide your tomato sauce between your pizza bases, then using the back of a #spoon{}, spread it over with swirling motions. Leave a 1cm gap around the edge.

Distribute your mozzarella over your pizzas, followed by your cherry tomatoes and olives. Finally pop your serrano ham pieces on top (they will go crispy in your oven if they are on top… yum!).

Grind over some black pepper and pop them in your oven for ~{15%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they aren't burning!

Get your washing up done and prepare for a pizza party!

When your pizzas are cooked (the cheese should be bubbling and the crust should be golden. Leave them in for a couple more mins if this isn't the case). Remove from your oven and tear over some basil leaves. Serve and enjoy!